    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2001860/extras/dafc36e0d7897e2cf7a86cd24f97961e.poster.avif?t=1766718076\" width=1080 height=500 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2001860/extras/dafc36e0d7897e2cf7a86cd24f97961e.webm?t=1766718076\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2001860/extras/dafc36e0d7897e2cf7a86cd24f97961e.mp4?t=1766718076\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Fishbait</strong> is a casual 2-4 player card game about survival where the last fish standing wins.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline crossorigin=\"anonymous\" poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2001860/extras/628489831d4dc8ac633664b559c02cb2.poster.avif?t=1766718076\" width=780 height=360 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2001860/extras/628489831d4dc8ac633664b559c02cb2.webm?t=1766718076\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >The gameplay utilizes Russian-roulette style mechanics, where a wrong draw can lead to your demise. The last thing you want as fish is be caught by the fisherman and turned into an all-you-can-eat sushi sampler.<br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2001860/extras/4b8e9c10f6d4189c808a7a42aef34683.avif?t=1766718076\" width=780 height=180 /></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Hidden among the deck are dangerous <strong>Bait</strong> cards. If you draw one, you’re immediately caught by the fisherman and lose the game—unless you have a way out.<br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2001860/extras/e843afaceb77943eb3d69a8cdc914e2f.avif?t=1766718076\" width=780 height=180 /></span>  If you have an <strong>Escape</strong> card, you may play it when you run into a Bait card. This lets you safely continue your turn. After escaping, you must place the Bait card back into the deck at a position of your choosing (top, 2nd, 3rd, bottom).<br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2001860/extras/c6156c6d8b20ab0cbaceb69212ef9979.avif?t=1766718076\" width=780 height=180 /></span>On your turn, you may play <strong>as many action cards as you want</strong>, in any order. Some examples are:</p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Alter</strong> – Rearrange the top three cards of the deck.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Favor</strong> – Force another player to give you a card of their choice.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Skip</strong> – Skip your turn</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Attack</strong> – Next player must draw 2 cards to end their turn </p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Nope</strong> – Cancel the effect of a card.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Reverse</strong> – Change the direction of play.</p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > Use these cards wisely to keep yourself off the dinner menu.<br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2001860/extras/bf7d910f19b6704bf9c8daa831c3ba87.avif?t=1766718076\" width=780 height=180 /></span><br>Your turn ends when you <strong>draw a card</strong>. This is normally from the top of the deck, but certain actions also count as your draw.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >For example, using <strong>Dig</strong> (draw the bottom card of the deck) <i>immediately ends your turn</i>.</p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p>",
